.TH UVA 1 "January 2026" "uvacompute 0.0.38" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
uva \- command-line interface for managing uvacompute virtual machines
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B uva
[\fB\-\-version\fR]
.I command
[\fIoptions\fR] [\fIarguments\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B uva
is the command-line interface for uvacompute, a cloud computing platform for provisioning and managing virtual machines with flexible resource configurations including CPU, RAM, disk, and GPU resources.
.PP
The CLI uses OAuth 2.0 device authorization flow for authentication and communicates with the uvacompute API to manage virtual machine lifecycles, SSH keys, and user sessions.
.SH COMMANDS
.SS Authentication
.TP
.B login
Authenticate with uvacompute using OAuth 2.0 device flow. Opens a browser window and prompts for authorization code entry.
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-force
Force re-authentication even if already logged in. Invalidates existing token and initiates new device authorization flow.
.RE
.TP
.B logout
Log out from uvacompute by removing the stored authentication token from local configuration.
.SS User Information
.TP
.B whoami
Display currently authenticated user information including name and email address.
.SS Virtual Machine Management
.TP
.B vm create
Create a new virtual machine with specified resource allocation.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-h ", " \-\-hours " \fIhours\fR"
(Required) Number of hours to run the VM. Must be a positive integer. VM will be automatically terminated after this duration.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-cpus " \fIcpus\fR"
Number of virtual CPUs (default: 1). Must be a power of 2. Maximum: 16.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-ram " \fIram\fR"
RAM allocation in gigabytes (default: 8). Must be a power of 2. Maximum: 64.
.TP
.BR \-d ", " \-\-disk " \fIdisk\fR"
Disk size in gigabytes (default: 64). Must be a power of 2. Maximum: 1000.
.TP
.BR \-g ", " \-\-gpus " \fIgpus\fR"
Number of GPUs to allocate (default: 0). Maximum: 1.
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-gpu-type " \fItype\fR"
GPU type (default: 5090). Currently only supports NVIDIA RTX 5090.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-name " \fIname\fR"
Optional friendly name for the VM. Used for identification and SSH connection. If a VM with this name already exists, the CLI prompts for confirmation before creating a duplicate.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-startup-script " \fIpath\fR"
Path to a bash script to run on first boot via cloud-init. Script executes as root during VM initialization. Maximum file size: 1MB. Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-\-cloud-init .
.TP
.BR \-\-cloud-init " \fIpath\fR"
Path to a custom cloud-init configuration file in YAML format. File must begin with '#cloud-config' header. SSH keys are automatically merged into the configuration. Maximum file size: 100KB. Mutually exclusive with
.BR \-\-startup-script .
.RE
.TP
.B vm delete \fInameOrVmId\fR
Delete a virtual machine by its ID or name. Immediately terminates and removes the VM. If multiple VMs share the same name, presents an interactive selection menu with an option to delete all matching VMs.
.TP
.B vm rm \fInameOrVmId\fR
Alias for
.BR "vm delete" .
Accepts VM ID or name. Supports interactive selection for duplicate names.
.TP
.B vm extend \fInameOrVmId\fR
Extend a running VM's expiration time by the specified number of hours. Only VMs in running state can be extended.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-\-hours " \fIhours\fR"
(Required) Number of hours to extend the VM. Must be a positive integer.
.RE
.TP
.B vm status \fIvmId\fR
Display current status and detailed information about a virtual machine including state, configuration, and any error messages.
.TP
.B vm list
List all running virtual machines owned by the authenticated user.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-all
Show all VMs regardless of status, including stopped, failed, expired, and deleted instances.
.RE
.TP
.B vm ls
Alias for
.BR "vm list" .
Accepts same options.
.TP
.B vm ssh \fInameOrVmId\fR
Connect to a virtual machine via SSH. Accepts either the VM ID or friendly name. If multiple VMs share the same name, presents an interactive selection menu. VM must be in running state. Requires SSH key to be configured.
.SS SSH Key Management
.TP
.B ssh-key add \fIpath\fR
Add an SSH public key for VM access. Reads public key from specified file path. ED25519 keys are recommended for better security and performance.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-name " \fIname\fR"
Friendly name for the SSH key (default: "Unnamed Key"). Used for identification in key listings.
.RE
.TP
.B ssh-key list
Display all SSH public keys associated with the authenticated user. Shows key ID, name, fingerprint, creation date, and primary status.
.TP
.B ssh-key ls
Alias for
.BR "ssh-key list" .
.TP
.B ssh-key remove \fIkeyId\fR
Remove an SSH public key by its ID. Prevents future use of this key for VM access.
.TP
.B ssh-key rm \fIkeyId\fR
Alias for
.BR "ssh-key remove" .
.TP
.B ssh-key set-primary \fIkeyId\fR
Set specified SSH key as the primary key. Primary key is used by default for new VM deployments.
.SS Container Job Management
.TP
.B run \fIimage\fR [\fIcommand...\fR]
Run a container job with the specified image. The optional command arguments are passed to the container.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-g ", " \-\-gpu
Request a GPU for the job. Allocates 1 GPU to the container.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-cpu " \fIcpus\fR"
Number of CPUs to allocate (default: 1). Maximum: 16.
.TP
.BR \-r ", " \-\-ram " \fIram\fR"
RAM allocation in gigabytes (default: 4). Maximum: 64.
.TP
.BR \-e ", " \-\-env " \fIKEY=VALUE\fR"
Set an environment variable in the container. Can be specified multiple times for multiple variables.
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-name " \fIname\fR"
Optional friendly name for the job. Used for identification in job listings.
.RE
.TP
.B jobs
List active container jobs (pending, scheduled, pulling, or running).
.RS
.TP
.BR \-a ", " \-\-all
Show all jobs regardless of status, including completed, failed, and cancelled jobs.
.TP
.BR \-s ", " \-\-status " \fIstatus\fR"
Filter jobs by status. Valid values: pending, scheduled, pulling, running, completed, failed, cancelled.
.RE
.TP
.B logs \fIjobId\fR
Display logs from a container job.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-t ", " \-\-tail " \fIlines\fR"
Show only the last N lines of log output.
.TP
.BR \-\-no-follow
Don't follow log output (this is currently the default behavior; streaming will be added in a future release).
.RE
.TP
.B cancel \fIjobId\fR
Cancel a running or pending job. Jobs in terminal states (completed, failed, cancelled) cannot be cancelled.
.SS Management
.TP
.B completion install
Install shell tab completion for the uva command. Supports Bash and Zsh shells. Automatically detects the current shell and configures completion scripts in the appropriate shell configuration file. After installation, restart your shell or source the configuration file to enable tab completion.
.TP
.B completion uninstall
Remove shell tab completion for the uva command. Cleans up completion scripts from shell configuration files and the tabtab directory.
.TP
.B upgrade
Upgrade the uvacompute CLI to the latest version. Checks the API for available updates, displays version comparison, and presents an interactive confirmation prompt (default: Yes) before downloading and installing the update. Automatically handles the upgrade process by running the official installation script. If binary replacement requires elevated permissions, provides instructions for using sudo.
.TP
.B uninstall
Uninstall the uvacompute CLI. Removes the CLI binary from the system and deletes all configuration data including authentication tokens. Presents an interactive confirmation prompt (default: No) before proceeding. If binary removal requires elevated permissions, displays instructions for manual removal.
.SS Node Management
.TP
.B node prepare [\-\-check] [\-\-skip\-iommu]
Prepare the system for node installation by installing NVIDIA drivers and checking IOMMU.
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Detects operating system (Ubuntu, Debian, Arch, Fedora, Gentoo)
.IP \(bu 2
Checks for NVIDIA GPU and installs appropriate driver
.IP \(bu 2
Verifies IOMMU is enabled for GPU passthrough
.IP \(bu 2
Saves preparation state for verification
.RE
.IP
Options:
.RS
.TP
.B \-\-check
Show what would be done without making changes (dry-run mode).
.TP
.B \-\-skip\-iommu
Skip IOMMU verification checks.
.RE
.IP
Requires root privileges (sudo) for driver installation. A system reboot is typically required after driver installation before proceeding with
.BR "node install" .
.TP
.B node install
Install k3s, KubeVirt, and configure the machine as a uvacompute contributor node. Requires that
.BR "node prepare"
has been run and the system rebooted if drivers were installed. Downloads and executes the installation script which handles:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
k3s (Kubernetes) installation
.IP \(bu 2
KubeVirt operator and CR deployment
.IP \(bu 2
NVIDIA container toolkit (if GPU detected)
.IP \(bu 2
GPU mode switching scripts generation
.IP \(bu 2
Node configuration state storage
.RE
.IP
Requires root privileges (sudo). Only Ubuntu and Debian are currently supported.
.TP
.B node uninstall
Remove all node components installed by
.BR "uva node install" .
This includes k3s, KubeVirt resources, GPU scripts, and configuration files. The nvidia-container-toolkit package is not removed automatically.
.TP
.B node status
Display current node status including:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Installation state and date
.IP \(bu 2
k3s status and version
.IP \(bu 2
KubeVirt deployment phase
.IP \(bu 2
GPU detection and current driver mode
.IP \(bu 2
Node scheduling status (active/paused)
.IP \(bu 2
Running workloads (VMs and Jobs)
.RE
.TP
.B node pause
Stop accepting new workloads on this node. Existing workloads continue running. Uses kubectl cordon under the hood.
.TP
.B node resume
Resume accepting new workloads on this node after being paused. Uses kubectl uncordon under the hood.
.TP
.B node config
Interactively configure resource sharing settings. Prompts for:
.RS
.IP \(bu 2
Number of CPUs to share
.IP \(bu 2
RAM allocation in GB
.IP \(bu 2
GPU sharing mode (container or none)
.RE
.IP
Configuration is saved to ~/.uvacompute/node/config.yaml.
.SS Remote Node Management
.TP
.B node list
List all nodes you have contributed to the uvacompute network. Displays node ID, name, status, resources, and last heartbeat.
.TP
.B node ls
Alias for
.BR "node list" .
.TP
.B node status \fInodeId\fR
Display status and detailed information about a specific remote node you own. Without a nodeId argument, shows local node status instead.
.TP
.B node pause \fInodeId\fR
Pause a remote node to stop accepting new workloads. Existing workloads continue running. Without a nodeId argument, pauses the local node instead.
.TP
.B node resume \fInodeId\fR
Resume a remote node to start accepting workloads again. Without a nodeId argument, resumes the local node instead.
.TP
.B node workloads \fInodeId\fR
Display active workloads (VMs and jobs) running on a specific remote node.
.SS Node Registration Tokens
.TP
.B node token create
Create a new node registration token for adding nodes to the network. Tokens are single-use and expire after 24 hours.
.RS
.TP
.BR \-n ", " \-\-name " \fIname\fR"
Optional name or description for the token.
.RE
.TP
.B node token list
List all registration tokens you have created, showing status (active, used, expired), assigned port, and creation date.
.TP
.B node token ls
Alias for
.BR "node token list" .
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.B \-\-version
Display CLI version number and exit.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.uvacompute/config
Configuration file storing authentication tokens, version information, completion prompt status, and last update check timestamp. JSON format. Created automatically on first login.
.TP
.I ~/.uvacompute/node/config.yaml
Node configuration file storing node ID, installation date, k3s version, and KubeVirt version. Created by
.BR "uva node install" .
.TP
.I ~/.uvacompute/node/install-state.yaml
Node installation state tracking file. Records installed components and GPU information for clean uninstallation.
.TP
.I ~/.uvacompute/node/prepare-state.yaml
System preparation state tracking file. Records OS information, GPU detection status, driver installation status, and IOMMU configuration. Created by
.BR "uva node prepare" .
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/gpu-mode-nvidia
Script to switch GPU to nvidia driver mode for container workloads. Created by
.BR "uva node install"
when an NVIDIA GPU is detected. Requires root privileges.
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/gpu-mode-vfio
Script to switch GPU to vfio-pci driver mode for VM passthrough. Created by
.BR "uva node install"
when an NVIDIA GPU is detected. Requires root privileges.
.TP
.I /usr/local/bin/gpu-mode-status
Script to display current GPU driver mode. Created by
.BR "uva node install"
when an NVIDIA GPU is detected.
.TP
.I ~/.config/tabtab/
Directory containing shell completion scripts for Bash and Zsh. Created when running
.BR "uva completion install" .
Shell configuration files (~/.bashrc or ~/.zshrc) are automatically updated to source these scripts.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Successful program execution.
.TP
.B 1
General error occurred. Check error message for details. Common causes include authentication failure, network errors, invalid parameters, or VM operation failures.
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Authentication
Login to uvacompute:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva login
.RE
.fi
.PP
Force re-authentication:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva login --force
.RE
.fi
.SS Basic VM Operations
Create a basic VM for 1 hour with default resources:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva vm create -h 1
.RE
.fi
.PP
Create a VM with custom CPU and RAM for 24 hours:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva vm create -h 24 -c 4 -r 16 -n training-vm
.RE
.fi
.PP
Create a GPU-accelerated VM for machine learning:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva vm create -h 12 -c 8 -r 32 -d 256 -g 1 -t 5090 -n ml-training
.RE
.fi
.PP
List all running VMs:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva vm list
.RE
.fi
.PP
List all VMs including stopped and expired:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva vm list --all
.RE
.fi
.PP
Check VM status:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva vm status abc-123-def
.RE
.fi
.PP
Delete a VM by ID:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva vm delete abc-123-def
.RE
.fi
.PP
Delete a VM by name (if multiple VMs share the name, interactive menu appears):
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva vm delete training-vm
.RE
.fi
.PP
Extend a running VM by 2 hours:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva vm extend training-vm --hours 2
.RE
.fi
.SS SSH Access
Connect to VM by name (if unique):
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva vm ssh training-vm
.RE
.fi
.PP
Connect to VM by ID:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva vm ssh abc-123-def
.RE
.fi
.SS SSH Key Management
Generate an ED25519 SSH key (recommended):
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"
.RE
.fi
.PP
Add SSH public key:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva ssh-key add ~/.ssh/id_ed25519.pub --name "My Laptop"
.RE
.fi
.PP
List all SSH keys:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva ssh-key list
.RE
.fi
.PP
Or using the shorthand:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva ssh-key ls
.RE
.fi
.PP
Remove SSH key:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva ssh-key remove key_abc123
.RE
.fi
.PP
Or using the shorthand:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva ssh-key rm key_abc123
.RE
.fi
.PP
Set primary SSH key:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva ssh-key set-primary key_abc123
.RE
.fi
.SS Container Jobs
Run a simple container job:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva run alpine echo "Hello, World!"
.RE
.fi
.PP
Run a Python script with environment variables:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva run python:3.11 python -c "import os; print(os.environ['MY_VAR'])" -e MY_VAR=hello
.RE
.fi
.PP
Run a GPU-accelerated job with custom resources:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva run --gpu --cpu 4 --ram 16 --name ml-training pytorch/pytorch python train.py
.RE
.fi
.PP
List active jobs:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva jobs
.RE
.fi
.PP
List all jobs including completed:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva jobs --all
.RE
.fi
.PP
Filter jobs by status:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva jobs --status running
.RE
.fi
.PP
View job logs:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva logs abc-123-def
.RE
.fi
.PP
View only the last 50 lines of logs:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva logs abc-123-def --tail 50
.RE
.fi
.PP
Cancel a running job:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva cancel abc-123-def
.RE
.fi
.SS Management
Enable tab completion for Bash or Zsh:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva completion install
.RE
.fi
.PP
Disable tab completion:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva completion uninstall
.RE
.fi
.PP
Upgrade to the latest version:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva upgrade
.RE
.fi
.PP
Uninstall the CLI and remove all configuration:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva uninstall
.RE
.fi
.SS Node Management
Prepare system for node installation:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node prepare
.RE
.fi
.PP
Check what prepare would do (dry-run):
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node prepare --check
.RE
.fi
.PP
Prepare without IOMMU checks:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node prepare --skip-iommu
.RE
.fi
.PP
Install as a contributor node (after prepare and reboot):
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node install
.RE
.fi
.PP
Check node status:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node status
.RE
.fi
.PP
Check GPU mode (after node install):
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ sudo gpu-mode-status
.RE
.fi
.PP
Switch GPU to container mode:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ sudo gpu-mode-nvidia
.RE
.fi
.PP
Switch GPU to VM passthrough mode:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ sudo gpu-mode-vfio
.RE
.fi
.PP
Uninstall node components:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node uninstall
.RE
.fi
.PP
Pause node (stop accepting new workloads):
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node pause
.RE
.fi
.PP
Resume node (accept workloads again):
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node resume
.RE
.fi
.PP
Configure resource sharing interactively:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node config
.RE
.fi
.SS Remote Node Management
List your contributed nodes:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node list
.RE
.fi
.PP
Or using the shorthand:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node ls
.RE
.fi
.PP
Check status of a specific remote node:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node status abc12345
.RE
.fi
.PP
Pause a remote node:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node pause abc12345
.RE
.fi
.PP
Resume a remote node:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node resume abc12345
.RE
.fi
.PP
View workloads on a remote node:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node workloads abc12345
.RE
.fi
.PP
Create a node registration token:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node token create --name "Home Server"
.RE
.fi
.PP
List registration tokens:
.PP
.nf
.RS
$ uva node token list
.RE
.fi
.SH DIAGNOSTICS
The CLI uses OAuth 2.0 device authorization flow. During login, if browser does not open automatically, manually visit the displayed URL and enter the provided code.
.PP
Tab completion can be enabled by running
.B uva completion install
which supports Bash and Zsh shells. After installation, restart your shell or run
.B source ~/.bashrc
(or
.BR ~/.zshrc )
to activate completion. Tab completion provides command, subcommand, flag, and dynamic suggestions for VM names, job IDs, node IDs, and option values (e.g., job status). Completion requires authentication and fetches current resources from the API with a 500ms timeout. Job completion for
.B cancel
only shows cancellable jobs (pending, scheduled, pulling, running). Node completion for
.B pause
only shows pausable nodes (online, offline) and for
.B resume
only shows resumable nodes (draining).
.PP
VM creation may take several minutes. The CLI polls status through the following stages:
.B creating
->
.B initializing
->
.B starting
->
.B waiting_for_agent
->
.B configuring
->
.BR running .
If creation fails, status will show
.B failed
with error details.
.PP
SSH connections require at least one SSH public key to be configured. Use
.B ssh-key add
to register your public key before attempting SSH access. ED25519 keys are recommended over RSA for better security and performance. Generate an ED25519 key with:
.B ssh-keygen -t ed25519 -C "your_email@example.com"
.PP
When multiple VMs share the same name, commands that accept VM names (
.BR ssh ,
.BR delete ,
.BR rm )
present an interactive selection menu. Use arrow keys to navigate and Enter to select. For
.B delete
operations, an additional option to delete all matching VMs is provided.
.PP
Version checks occur automatically once per 24 hours. Update notifications display latest version and upgrade instructions. To upgrade at any time, run:
.B uva upgrade
